Intel 8086 VS Polish communist MERA-400 CPU (evolution of Karpiński K-202 arch)
text:
Video from channel of an owner and restoration hobbyist from Poland who owns and runs a working (as far as age and quality of socialist era components allows it) unit of that computer. Mera-400 is a descendant of legendary K-202 architecture designed by Jacek Karpiński (Polish computer systems engineer known for analog and digital computers designs including his 1964 variant of Perceptron - early neural network type of computer).

More detailed article on Jacek Karpiński is available at English language wikipedia.

Mera-400 was notable for running CROOK operating system that was an OS influenced by UNIX.

Video with subtitles, you can use auto-translate to English: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H7gh1PEqVak

Show HN: Open two-sided marketplace for fitness classes
text:
Hi all,

We've built a mobile app for what we hope to be a platform for fitness instructors, students, and studios to connect. We'd love to have your feedback.

For students: We typically gather our wellness practices from a variety of sources. Rather than manage these sources independently, merge them with deepmove. Find your friends and your teachers and know where the best classes for your needs are, always.

For teachers: Your organizing platform is here. Your community, your communications, your calendar. No more separate accounts for every facet of your teaching. Let deepmove simplify operations so you can focus on what you do best.

For studios: Modernize your studio. Move from archaic systems behind the desk to a streamlined platform in a global marketplace. Cater to and interact with your clients and your teachers in a familiar format. Let your community shine. We’re just getting started!

Ask HN: What should I learn as a 42 year old designer looking to build web apps?
text:
I’m a designer who’s long been interested in the dev side, so this year I’ve decided to build a web app from scratch. Problem is, there’s so many different languages and frameworks it’s hard to know what I should focus on first.

What would be your recommendation for something that’s powerful, fairly easy to get started with and hopefully useful career-wise too.

I’m fluent in html/css and know a bit of Python and JavaScript, if that helps.
